epresents the earliest known Arabic notebook of an artisan or merchant.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aThis eBook is made available Open Access under a CC BY 4.0 license: uhttps://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0  aIn Arabic.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Middle Eastern.2bisacsh1 aLiebrenz, Boris, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aRichardson, Kristina L., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1z978311117578208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2023z9783111318912oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2023z9783111318820oZDB-23-DGF0 cprintz978311068887040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9783110688924zOpen Access7040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110688924zOpen Access70423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110688924/original  a978-3-11-117578-2 DG Plus DeG Package 2023 Part 1b2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aZDB-23-DGFb2023  aZDB-23-DGGb2023  aZDB-23-GOA